===Etymology===
As this word appeared in texts about ancient Eastern Yue (now Min) area and Chen Zan remarked that it was a {{w|Wu (state)|Wu}}-{{w|Yue (state)|Yue}} word, {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} speculates that it has {{bor|zh|aav}} origin, comparing it to Wa-Lawa-Bulang *''rah'' "rapids, waterfall" & {{cog|mkh-okm|rat||to move swiftly, to run}}, possibly derived from a root meaning "swift". {{cog|zhx-min-pro|*l̥aiC}} is identical to {{cog|tai-pro|*hla:iB1}}.

Possibly unrelated to {{och-l|濿}} "a ford".

